in the two columns are vertically out of synch after this point.",{"_":31,"ana":32,"ref":33},"chiselled","#execution.chiselled","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/writing/lod/1",{"ana":35},"#text_condition.partly_illegible",{"lettering":37,"dimensions":38},"Neatly carved and regular letters, mostly without serifs, but some terminal wedges. Alpha with straight bar; epsilon on occasion has a slightly shorter mid-bar; zeta in form of I with wide horizontals; theta has short detached cross-bar; kappa has full-length arms; mu has vertical first and last, full length mid-strokes; xsi has three equal horiztonal bars; omicron is only slightly smaller than the other letters; pi has extended horizontal; rho has small rounded closed eye; sigma has horizontal top and bottom, with slihgtly variable mid-strokes; phi has small oval eye, with vertical often extended; omega is notably variable, always closed, but ranging from tear-drop to full circle on or even above and detached from the base line.",[39,45,50],{"type":40,"l":41,"from":42,"to":42,"h":43,"unit":44},"letterHeight","Line 1","line1","18","mm",{"type":40,"l":46,"from":47,"to":48,"h":49,"unit":44},"Line 2-23","line2","line23","11-15 (with omicron down to 9 and phi up to 20)",{"type":51,"l":52,"from":53,"to":47,"unit":44},"interlinear","Interlineation line 1 to 2","line",{"_":55,"notBefore":56,"notAfter":57,"evidence":58},"Later third or second century BCE on palaeographic grounds.",-250,-101,"lettering",[60,64],{"_":61,"type":62,"ref":63},"Acrae","ancient","http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/462068",{"_":65,"type":66,"ref":67,"offset":68},"Palazzolo Acreide","modern","http://sws.geonames.org/2523922","near",[70],[71,72],37.0578,14.89346,[],"Italy","Sicily",{"_":77,"role":78,"ref":79},"Museo Archeologico Gabriele Judica","museum","http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/museum/102",{"_":81,"type":82},"2238","inventory",{"_":84,"mainLang":85,"languages":86},"Ancient Greek","grc",[84],"492659",{"n":89,"url":90,"height":91,"width":92,"des